args:
With Thanatos's underlings defeated, the prince
proposes to Felicia that they take the fight to the
fiend himself. Though hesitant at first, she soon
decides to fight in order to earn true freedom.
Together, she and the party head into the space
between worlds to challenge her former captor.
Why do you refuse to accept me,\nmy beloved dancer? Why do you\nshun me when I love you so?
Your place is at my side, for you've\nno other home to return to.
You are mine. Never forget this!
I can't hear his voice anymore.
All trace of Thanatos seems to have\nvanished. It appears we are out\nof any immediate trouble.
Oh, Cleo! Are you truly all right?!
I amâ€”and I'm sorry to have worried you.
I'm the one who should be apologizing.
That's rightâ€”it's that Thanatos punk\nwe've got beef with!
Notte and Cleo are both right,\nso don't blame yourself, okay?
Now let's get a move on.\nYour hometown awaits!
If I return home, Thanatos might\nput a curse on another villager.\nOr maybe even ALL of them!
I can't keep putting others in\ndanger for my sake.
But what will you do? Go back to him?
Fight Thanatos?! But that would be...
No. This plan is far too dangerous.\nHaving challenged Thanatos before,\nI know well his strength.
But what's the other option, then? Flee?\nA life spent on the run is no life at all.
You will never know peace if you merely\nattempt to escape his grasp.
She's in danger whether she runs or fights.\nThat's all there is to it.
You understood that from the beginning,\ndidn't you Felicia?
But even knowing he would pursue you,\nyou still chose to escape. There must\nhave been a reason.
Ah, Felicia, my sweet.\nYou dance as beautifully as ever.
Thanatos, I have a request:\nPlease return me to my village.
Your place is at my side, my beloved.
Forget your village. Dance for me alone,\nand make this your new happiness.
I wanted to go back to my home.\nTo see my family and friends.
I wanted to dance freely, the way I used to.
Then fight. Because until you do,\nyou're always going to be a prisoner.
If you do nothing but run, you'll never\nknow true freedom.
Your words have the ring of truth,\n{player_name}.
I believed the best course of action\nwas to assist in her escape...but it\nseems I was mistaken.
You take care of Felicia.\nI will go to war with Thanatos.
Hold on, pal! You're gonna run off\nand take on Thanatos by yourself?
The fight with him will be truly fierce.\nAnd I cannot allowâ€”
No, Phantom. I'm going to fight, too.
I don't want to be shackled by my fear\nof Thanatos anymore.
No. It is far too dangerous.
I can't just let you keep fighting\nmy battles for me, Phantom!
Hey, here's a total genius idea:\nMaybe we should ALL fight.
Like I always say, the more the merrier!\n...Except in line at a buffet, in which\ncase I want it to be just me.
But if the tide turns against us, she will be\nthere for Thanatos to snatch away anew!
So let's fight together and get home\nsafelyâ€”ALL of us.
Very well. We shall fight together.
So now that we've settled that,\nhow exactly are we supposed to GET\nto wherever Thanatos is hanging out?
I took these from the fiends earlier.\nI believe they will answer your question.
Otherworld fragments, yes. They contain a\npowerful mana that can warp space itself.
Perhaps Thanatos had his underlings take\nsome with them in order to bring me back?
Which means we can use them\nto go wherever he's hiding.
Precisely. Now let us be off.
So this is where Thanatos dwells...
This place has a foul air about it.\nI like it not.
I hear the echoes of moans...\nI cannot believe you were trapped\nin such a terrible place.
Urrgh... That mana he's exuding\nis making me sick to my stomach.
Are these others an apology offering to\nme, Felicia? A truly faithful act.
I'm not returning to you, Thanatos.
I've come here to defeat you!
What was that you said, my dancer?
I've come here to defeat you and\nreclaim my freedom for good!
Ah, but you are delightful, Felicia!\nHave you taken leave of your senses?

More importantly, will you still stand as
strong as you do now even after I have
drained the life from your comrades
before your very eyes?
And what can you do, weak and frail\nas you are?
Not just me, but all of us! So long as there\nis passion inside us, we cannot lose!
You've acted without care or thought of\nothers for too long, and it ends here!
You will die with those words lodged\nin your throat, cur!
I won't let you hurt anyone else!
You would oppose me to the very end?\nHmph. Very well!
If you would prattle on about ending me,\nthen so be it! Come forth! You will dance\nuntil you die!
